(140, 'Tsinjovy(Balsam)', 'Tsinjovy(Balsam)\\n\\n 1_Tsinjovy anie ny lanitra\\n Misy ireo voronkely marobe izay tsy mahay ny \\nmamafy na mitahiry an_tsompitra re!\\n Fa ny Ray Tsitoha miahy azy\\n Ka dia tsy misy ahiany\\n\\n Ref:koa nahoana ianao\\n No manahy ny ho avy\\n Moa va tsy mino ny fonao\\n Fa omeny izay ilainao\\n\\n 2_Zahao koa eny an-tsaha\\n Misy ireo voninkazo marobe\\n Toy reny ny lisy,ny raozy koa\\n Mitafy lokon\'andriandehibe\\n\\n Ref..\\n 3_dinihonao reo namanao\\n Izay samy manana ny endriny\\n Satria tsy iray ny fiaviny\\n Samy hafa koa ny fisainany\\n Fa ny Ray Tsitoha sady mpiahy\\n tsy manavaka fa mampiray\\n\\n Ref..\\n tapitra fin'),
(141, 'Ako farany OBEY', 'Ako farany OBEY\\n\\n Give me your O, O!\\n Give me your B, B!\\n Give me your E, E!\\n Give me your Y, Y!\\n And what\'s that\'s spelling?\\n\\n OBEY!!!!\\n Oh yeah!\\n O B E Y\\n obey your mum and dad\\n O B E Y\\n Makes them very glad\\n Listen to the words they say\\n Obey your parents every day\\n O B E Y\\n Obey your mum and dad\\n (one more time!)\\n\\n O B E Y\\n Obey your mum and dad....\\n (OK, now here is something you can practice)\\n When your riding in the car sing still (Sing still)\\n When your mum says go to bed say I will (I will)\\n When it\'s time to clean your room,\\n you must pick up your toys\\n Remember that obey brings joy\\n (Oh!)\\n\\n OBEY\\n Obey your mum and dad....\\n (God loves it when you listen!)\\n When mum and dada say tell the truth, don\'t lie (don\'t lie!)\\n When they say you have an oath, don\'t cry (don\'t cry!)\\n \'Cause when you do the things you should,\\n you\'ll find out it\'s true\\n Obey, n\'the end, is very good for you\\n (oh!)\\n\\n O B E Y\\n Obey your mum and dad....\\n (x2) (OBEY!!!!!!!!!!!!!)\\n O B E Y\\n Obey your mum and dad....\\n Listen to the words they say\\n Obey your parents every day\\n O B E Y\\n Obey your mum and dad!\\n (Yeah, do it! oh yeah!!!!)\\n'),
(142, '***AOKA IZAY***', '***AOKA IZAY***\\n\\n Aoka izay reo fanaratsiana\\n Endrikendrika fomba fanao\\n Aoka izay fa tsy hanatsara ny fanahinao\\n Ampy izay ny fifosafosana\\n bitsibitsika ny namanao\\n Aoka izay aoka izay\\n Dia ovay re ny fomba fanao\\n\\n  Ngamba ianao tsy mahatsapa fa ireny\\n Dia mamono na dia hoe teny\\n Fa tena marary mandratra fo manimba tokoa\\n Tsy aleo ve teny mba mampahery\\n Mampitodika ireo mino very\\n Dia ho hitanao fa hamonjy azy ireo teny natao\\n\\n  Ndeha ialana reo hita fa ratsy\\n Fifankatiavana no hajoro\\n Avelao any ireny fa toa mampikoro\\n Ny firaisana no aoka ho hita\\n Zay kinasa rehetra dia ho vita\\n Tsy ho ela dia io fa ho tody soa ny dia\\n tapitra fin'),
